snippet.textDisplay: It’s normal during these times to argue, just take it easy on your wife as becoming a mother is extremely stressful and has an impact on her in ways a man can never understand or feel. Having a baby is not easy and the recovery from having a baby both physical and psychological can take over a year post partum. Be careful whilst arguing with the mother of your daughter in front of your daughter as you are showing her how a man should treat her, very very important you set an example of respect, empathy and care for her mother so she will be able to pick a man that will support not make her life hell. Best of luck. Me and my husband been through it with our first our son & I promise you when you learn to grow up and not let passive aggression induce a unhealthy reaction out of you it’ll be calmmmmm. Just remember every time you shout to or around your child it alters the structure of their brain permanently and can damage them in ways we’ll never know. So just think of your child first and you think about giving her a good chance at life by not effin her up in head. I say this from experience so please try to understand a nuclear family is better than a broken distant one so try not to give up too early.

snippet.textDisplay: Separation isn’t divorce and it shouldn’t be thought of as an end to marriage.
